
                                                                   rationalp


    FUNCTION
    rationalp  -  test whether an object is a rational number

    USAGE
    rationalp object

    DESCRIPTION
    Returns true if OBJECT is a ratio or an integer,  and  false  otherwise.
    The following identity holds:

    (rationalp x) = (typep x 'rational)

    EXAMPLES
    (rationalp 1.3) => nil
    (rationalp 1/3) => t
    (rationalp 3) => t
    (rationalp 3.4) => nil

    SEE ALSO
    CLtL 6:74, about type specifiers, integer, ration, rational










































